725049f-a.title: Queens: 18th Street - 27th Avenue
725049f-a.text:
18th Street, north from 27th Avenue. Note in the back-
ground the tower of the Triborough Bridge and the arc of the
Hellgate Bridge. 18th Street was formerly Willow Street.
P. L. Sperr  June 12, 1935

725161f-a.title: Queens: 27th Avenue - 18th Street
725161f-a.text:
27th Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 18th Street, showing
an old frame house with stucco front. It is used as a ateam-
ship ticket office by N. and M. Daddario.
P. L. Sperr  June 12, 1935
